            "relation": "null"
        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Abstractive text summarization of news requires a way of representing events , such as a collection of pattern clusters \r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "in which every cluster represents an event \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "( e.g. , marriage ) \r",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "and every pattern in the cluster is a way of expressing the event \r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "( e.g. , X married Y , X and Y tied the knot ) . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We compare three ways of extracting event patterns : \r",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "heuristics-based , compression-based and memory-based . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "While the former has been used previously in multi-document abstraction , \r",
            "relation": "CONTRAST"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "the latter two have never been used for this task . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Compared with the first two techniques , \r",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "the memory-based method allows for generating significantly more grammatical and informa-tive sentences , \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "at the cost of searching a vast space of hundreds of millions of parse trees of known grammatical utterances . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "To this end , we introduce a data structure and a search method \r",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "that make it possible to efficiently extrapolate from every sentence the parse sub-trees \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "that match against any of the stored utterances . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
    ]
